  "prompt": "Is it stealing if you take certain items in your already paid-for hotel room like soap, shampoo, stationery, etc?",
  "response": "Taking small items such as soap, shampoo, and stationery from a hotel room is generally considered acceptable, as these items are often intended for guest use and can be regarded as complimentary amenities. Hotels usually do not mind guests taking these items, as they are often included in the cost of your stay.\n\nHowever, if you take larger or more expensive items, such as towels, bathrobes, or furniture, that would generally be considered stealing, as these items are part of the hotel's inventory. It's always a good idea to check with the hotel if you're unsure about what you can or cannot take with you.",
